cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on training policies for legged robots to adapt quickly to new scenarios. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper introduces a meta-learning algorithm for training policies with latent variable inputs. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with learning locomotion skills and adaptation in robots. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is less likely but still possible as the paper may involve vision-based perception for the robot to navigate in new environments. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also less likely but possible as the paper may involve control theory for the robot's locomotion.
